text: Sykies (), formerly Sykeai (Συκέαι), is a community and village in the municipal unit of Fyllo, municipality of Palamas, periphery of Karditsa, Thessaly, Greece. As of the census of 2011, the community had a population of 294, while the village had a population of 257. The community has two villages, Sykies and Magoulitsa (Μαγουλίτσα). Within the bounds of Sykies is the site of the ancient city of Asterium. ==References== Category:Populated places in Karditsa (regional unit)
title: Sykies, Karditsa
